        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`layer.path` from `architecture-rules.json` is joined directly into `root.join(...).join(\"src\")` with no containment check, so a malformed or malicious layer entry can escape the trusted root (for example `../..` or an absolute path) and make the verifier scan arbitrary files outside the workspace.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/syn_scan.rs",
              "line": 77,
              "category": "trusted-root violation"
            },
            {
              "message": "The directory walk reads and recurses through entries with plain `read_dir`, `path.is_dir()`, and `read_to_string()` but never rejects symlinks at the boundary, so a symlink under `src/` can redirect the scan outside the workspace. This breaks the real-file semantics used elsewhere for trusted-root loaders.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/syn_scan.rs",
              "line": 98,
              "category": "symlink not rejected at boundary"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:a83d0b82cdada70c245adb5a0abff76897cbee4d59956fc0fc4caa95bd59a707",
          "at": "2026-06-26T11:32:14Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:ad7fdd873270974747ad0d1167cb5f14b7ddfbf32567f12532eecfeca62fc1a5",
          "at": "2026-06-26T11:39:51Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "File-backed modules are never resolved here. A crate with `#[cfg(test)] mod tests;` and a separate `tests.rs` under `src/` will still have that file scanned, so `#[doc(hidden)]` inside a test-only module can be reported as a violation. This breaks the stated `cfg(test) mod foo;` exclusion and needs module-file resolution or an equivalent skip map.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/syn_scan.rs",
              "line": 320,
